Aberrant origin of the right coronary artery as a potential cause of sudden death: successful anatomical correction.
 A man with an aberrant right coronary artery and haemodynamically important prolapse of the mitral valve was successfully resuscitated.
 The aberrant right coronary artery was thought to be a possible cause of the cardiopulmonary arrest in this patient.
 Both lesions were corrected at a single operation.
